    "map_url": "https://www.google.com/maps?q=-11.7,171.8",
    "official_link": "https://www.google.com/maps?q=-11.7,171.8",
    "country_code": null,
    "payload": {
      "item_type": "disturbance",
      "source": "jtwc_abpw",
      "source_key": "jtwc_abpw|south_pacific_area|invest_91p",
      "content_hash": "afe3a4dcf322c621",
      "platform_summary": "11.7S 171.8E | winds 28-33 kt | 1002 mb | MEDIUM",
      "platform_location": "11.7S 171.8E",
      "wind": "28-33 kt",
      "risk_48h": null,
      "risk_7d": null,
      "next_update": null,
      "raw_text": "(1) THE AREA OF CONVECTION (INVEST 91P) PREVIOUSLY LOCATED NEAR \n12.4S 170.8E IS NOW LOCATED NEAR 11.7S 171.8E, APPROXIMATELY 347 NM \nNORTH-NORTHEAST OF PORT VILLA. MULTISPECTRAL SATELLITE IMAGERY (MSI) \nREVEALS A BROAD LOW LEVEL CIRCULATION CENTER (LLCC) WITH AN ELONGATED \nBUT SLOWLY CONSOLIDATING CENTER. A RECENT OSCAT-3 PASS REVEALED A \nBROAD CIRCULATION WITH A BAND OF ELEVATED WINDS UP TO 30 KNOTS ALONG \nTHE EASTERN FLANK OF THE ROTATION. ENVIRONMENTAL ANALYSIS REVEALS \nFAVORABLE CONDITIONS FOR DEVELOPMENT WITH LOW TO MODERATE VERTICAL \nWIND SHEAR (15-20 KNOTS), GOOD DIFFLUENT OUTFLOW ALOFT, AND WARM SEA \nSURFACE TEMPERATURES (29-30 C). GLOBAL MODELS ARE IN FAIR AGREEMENT \nTHAT INVEST 91P WILL CONTINUE TO HAVE STEADY DEVELOPMENT AND A \nSOUTHWESTWARD TRACK OVER THE NEXT 24 TO 36 HOURS. MAXIMUM SUSTAINED \nSURFACE WINDS ARE ESTIMATED AT 28 TO 33 KNOTS. MINIMUM SEA LEVEL \nPRESSURE IS ESTIMATED TO BE NEAR 1002 MB. THE POTENTIAL FOR THE \nDEVELOPMENT OF A SIGNIFICANT TROPICAL CYCLONE WITHIN THE NEXT 24 HOURS \nIS UPGRADED TO MEDIUM.",
      "metadata": {
        "basin_section": "SOUTH PACIFIC AREA (WEST COAST OF SOUTH AMERICA TO 135 EAST)",
        "invest_id": "91P",
        "lat": -11.7,
        "lon": 171.8,
        "wind_kt_min": 28,
        "wind_kt_max": 33,
        "pressure_mb": 1002,
        "development_phrase": "UPGRADED TO",
        "development_level": "MEDIUM",
        "bulletin_issue_at": "2026-04-04T06:00:00+00:00"
      }
    },
